  "body": "Following the discussion here: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4230#discussion_r1189475825\r\n\r\nThe following workflow is currently possible:\r\n\r\n- The admin initiate a default admin transfer\r\n- Using the internal _revoke, the dev (admin?) renounce its admin position. \r\n  - This emits the revoke event, and set the current admin to `address(0)`\r\n    - At the point users will think the contract has no admin, and will not get a new one\r\n- The pending admin accepts, and \"resurrect\" the admin rights\r\n  - This goes against the expectation (by the user) that the admin was removed from the system.\r\n  \r\nIf we consider that a security issue, a possible fix is described [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4230#discussion_r1189478106)\r\n",
